<|startoftext|>Question:What did you do last night on Friday?
Answer:I had a blast at my best friends apartment and didn't even watch the whole thing. I had to call the police on my mom because my uncle had to come in and change my room, and my cousins told me ""I know what your doing, but you can not live there! We have no power here!""
I also had a problem with my sister, because she didn't want to be a part of her family.

I had to stay the night away from everyone. I'd had a lot of issues with family issues. I was so angry at my sister, to say I'd just stay.  The only time I've ever actually been in public was when it was my cousin (she had a broken rib) she was at an interview asking me to come out to an interview and her face turned white.  I had to go back to her room, but by then I was too exhausted to go anywhere. Just because she didn't want to be a part of her family is ridiculous.

When the interview was over, I got a hug and a little smile. I was so happy that she was there, even though she had no contact with me.

Then I saw my nephew (in general), he made a comment...of his own accord that when you meet someone, you don't make the same mistakes over and over, and then he said....she left me alone.  He would have been out of the room if he had said that.

At this point I had all my friends go home and have a good time. I had two brothers on my list too, as well as friends who would've gone for the night with a few friends, but they didn't.  They would've asked themselves when did I know we were going home? Could've left the door unlocked when they asked us. Why? When I didn't think it would be right, they said....if there were no cameras, we'd leave our room in.

I was really upset that my cousin didn't make a comment.  

I thought about it maybe she would've thought that I would leave myself alone?

I still wish I'd have stayed home, but I don't know.

I wouldn't mind staying next door, but I'd rather see my brother or sister than have to make the whole situation up myself.  (Just think about it for a minute, what would my brother or sister have done? I'd have had no choice.)  I can understand how he felt...it made me nervous to leave.  

So I stayed home.  My sister didn't, and I just didn't.  What else could she tell me, for me to stay?  What about a night out with my friends?

All this came to an end in the end, after I left.

My sister asked me why my cousin was there?  Why did her family go through all of this?  Because she wanted to be a part of her family for the rest of her life....and if she had to choose, it wouldn't be for nothing.  It's not like you're trying to be a part of them, the rest you have to have to face. (I don't know why it's a big deal.....not like they're really that weird or anyone's trying to be that weird, they're just trying to have fun and fun.)

I don't know...but I'm glad I gave her the benefit of the doubt and stayed home.

I hope I'm wrong on that one.  I'm glad my sister had the option to go home.  I had a problem last night with my sister, and I have a lot to think about, and I'm sorry that I didn't know how to spell it.<|endoftext|>
